Spreadsheet Applications – Solved Slips
Macro Steps and Output
1.Open Microsoft Excel.
2.Click File → Options.
3.Select Customize Ribbon.
4.Tick the Developer option and click OK.
5.Open Developer tab.
6.Click Visual Basic or press Alt + F11.
7.Click Insert → Module.
8.Type the macro code:
Sub CheckValue()
If Range("A1").Value > 70 Then
MsgBox "Greater than 70"
End If
End Sub
9.Press Ctrl + S to save file.
10.Save as Excel Macro-Enabled Workbook (.xlsm).
11.Enter any number in cell A1.
Example: 85
12.Go to Developer → Macros.
13.Select CheckValue macro.
14.Click Run.
Output :
If value in A1 is greater than 70, message box displays:
“Greater than 70”

